installing java and maven building and testing maven:
first install java,
sudo apt update




Step 1: Download the jdk Binaries
https://download.java.net


Step 2 setiing up java_home and the path enviroment variables

Step 3 Verify the java installations
Java --verson



Now install setup maven:
sudo apt install maven
https://maven.apache.org/guides/getting-started/maven-in-five-minutes.html

# to check maven version
mvn --version

create a simple project and run maven
mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.mycompany.app -DartifactId=my-app -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DarchetypeVersion=1.4 -DinteractiveMode=false

mvn clean will delete the Target
mvn package will restore the Target
